text: Paul Tjøstolsen Sunde (5 February 1896 - 2 September 1958) was a Norwegian politician for the Labour Party. He was born in Nissedal. He was elected to the Norwegian Parliament from the Market towns of Telemark and Aust-Agder counties in 1945, and was re-elected on one occasion. Sunde was a member of Arendal city council from 1931 to 1934, and of its executive committee in the periods 1937-1940 and 1955-1958\. ==References== * Category:1896 births Category:1958 deaths Category:Labour Party (Norway) politicians Category:Members of the Storting Category:20th-century Norwegian politicians
